    "background": "Suppose that $X_1, X_2, \\ldots, X_n$ are independent random variables, each with the uniform distribution on $[c-d, c+d]$ where $c$ and $d$ are both unknown $(-\\infty<c<\\infty, d>0)$. Additionally, given failure time data: $20,23,25,26,28,29,31,33,34$, and 35 days, assume the data follow a uniform distribution on [$c-d, c+d$].",
    "data": null,
    "question": "Find the maximum likelihood estimators of $c$ and $d$ for the uniform distribution on $[c-d, c+d]$."
  },
